      "writtenOn": "2019-11-16T15:44:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "actually, thinking about this more. A piece of JSON\n\n{\n  \"resultdb\": {\n    \"test_results\": {\n       \"port\": 1234,\n       \"auth_token\": \"hello\"\n     }\n  }\n}\n\n\nmakes less sense than\n\n{\n  \"resultdb\": {\n    \"resultsink\": {\n       \"port\": 1234,\n       \"auth_token\": \"hello\"\n     }\n  }\n}\n\nbecause test results do not have a port. A resultsink does because it is a server.\nWDYT?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 29,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 29,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "2784f35550cf3d7370581776bbbaced1264b21ef",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
